does anyone has a upstairs neighbor from hell my upstairs neighbor is the neighbor from hell she puts tile floors through out her condo and walks around all day and night with heels on tile offers no insulation from noise i have spoken to her written her notes about the noise but nothing works she drags the furniture on the floor and drops things on the floor all hours of the day and night she is a older woman living alone i expected her to be in bed by pm instead she is like the living dead up all night and day slaming the cabinet doors for minitues non stop i have not taken a vacation because i don't travel and the thought of being home everyday listening to her noise is unbearable i can't afford to move and i like the location it is convenient i tried to be friendly and cordial to her but the noise continues any ideas if your building has an hov you may want to look into the rules and make sure when the upstairs neighbor installed the tile flooring she also took steps to have the floor properly sound proofed the building i live in has this requirement you could also bring it up at the next homeowners association meeting if you have a homeowners association if however you don't have either of those options then a shoe wrapped in a plastic bag pounding on your ceiling her floor everytime she makes too much noise works well you can also try a stereo speaker pointed at the ceiling and placed as close to it as possible turned up extremely loud helps too when she's clunking around in her high heels try going up knocking on the door and just looking at her then down at her shoes back at her face with a little bit of a crazed look in your eyes and asking if she could at least take her shoes off while walking around can often get the point across the main thing is fight fire with fire she makes noise you make noise right back at her if she comes down and complains to you about the noise you're making play dumb and say i have no idea what you're talking about or blame it o